comments: Beal (WAS) makes marginal contact with Doncic's (DAL) arm, which doesn't affect his driving shot attempt.
Porzingis (DAL) legally contests Beal's (WAS) driving shot attempt.
Kleber (DAL) makes clean contact with the ball before incidental contact occurs with Gafford (WAS) during the rebound.

Gafford (WAS) pursues the rebound and as he comes down, incidental contact occurs with Hardaway Jr. (DAL) during the rebound. Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Kleber (DAL) makes marginal contact with Avdija (WAS) during the off-ball screen.
Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) leg extends slightly after his release and creates marginal contact that does not affect Avdija's (WAS) ability to defend the shot.
Kleber (DAL) and Avdija (WAS) engage and separate off-ball.
Bullock (DAL) is drawn vertically into the air when marginal body contact occurs as Kuzma (WAS) leans into him on the perimeter.
Kleber (DAL) commits a take foul on Caldwell-Pope (WAS).
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that the foul occurred prior to the game clock expiring. Porzingis (DAL) pushes Kuzma (WAS) in the back and affects his SQBR.
